track_notes:
8.25m (13.25km) with 3415ft (1041m) ascent.
A walk done in August 2010 from Seatoller Farm (B&B). You use the old road to reach Honister Hause and then head up to Grey Knotts and Brandreth (Wainwrights). From Beck Head it is a scramble up to LD-005 GREAT GABLE. Then down to Windy Gap to next visit Green Gable (Wainwright). The easiest way back (I imagine) is down Gillercombe. If you decide to traverse Base Brown (Wainwright) expect a steep and slighty risky descent off it. The only casualty when we did this was my friends Leki pole which broke his fall and snapped in two. It probably saved Geoff a personal injury...
track_title: Great Gable from Seatoller Farm with four extra Wainwrights

track_notes: This track takes you up the mining road from Honister Slate mine and then across to Moses Trodd before ascending Great Gable from the North-Westerly corner. The descent via Windy Gap then takes in the Wainwrights of Green Gable, Brandreth and Grey Knotts before ending back at Honister Pass.
track_title: Great Gable from Honister Pass with 3 additional Wainwrights

track_notes: Total time (including ops): 7hr 25m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T2. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards.
